title: JS Social: In-Person -  Job Seekers’ Event with Morgan McKinley
details:
Details
-------

_**\*\* REGISTRATION IS CLOSED NOW \*\***_  
_**\*\* WE HAVE A FULL HOUSE! THANK YOU FOR YOUR INTEREST :)\*\***_

**TorontoJS June In-person Social Event**  
TJS Job Seekers’ Event with Morgan McKinley

\==================================================

Junior-dev focused job seekers’ event for Toronto JS members.  
Includes Interview Preparation info session presented by recruiters of Morgan McKinley - technology recruitment agency.  
We will offer resume / portfolio review by members of TorontoJS, professional developers with many years of experience.

QnA session will be followed after the Job search and interview prep presentation delivered by recruiters of Morgan McKinley.  
The recruiters will also be available for a short 1:1 consultation on first-come-first-serve basis.

Light refreshments and snacks provided.

If you are interested in attending this event, you can find the detailed event information **[here](https://docs.google.com/document/d/e/2PACX-1vSQYaYHAsMZKzBZ7cugR-4UXmrmjdqUI5xBJIZAnVwEij_AC-zVhJojr85FfQm7KJ38cllLsb0Rhgxk/pub) .(THE EVENT IS AT FULL CAPACITY NOW! REGISTRATION IS CLOSED. )**

Please be aware your registration will not be complete until you submit the google form that is available at the end of the event description page!

Attendees who would like to participate in the reviewing session need to submit their resume and portfolio when they register for the event.

If you have any questions, please join us our slack channel through TorontoJS [website](https://torontojs.com/) and look for organizers! :)

P.S. TorontoJS is migrating to \[[Guild.host](http://Guild.host)\]([https://guild.host/torontojs/events](https://guild.host/torontojs/events)) as our new home! Please consider joining us there, as new events will be only available for sign up at the guild platform in the future.

Code of conduct is enforced at all TorontoJS events [https://torontojs.com/p/code\_of\_conduct](https://torontojs.com/p/code_of_conduct)
